  "prompt": "What is the formula to calculate a synchronous speed of a motor?",
  "response": "The synchronous speed of an AC motor can be calculated using the following formula:\n\n\\[ N_s = \\frac{120 \\times f}{P} \\]\n\nwhere:\n- \\( N_s \\) is the synchronous speed in revolutions per minute (RPM),\n- \\( f \\) is the frequency of the AC power supply in hertz (Hz),\n- \\( P \\) is the number of poles in the motor.\n\nTo use this formula, you need to know the frequency of the electrical supply and the number of poles in the motor. For example, in a system with a frequency of 60 Hz and a motor with 4 poles, the synchronous speed would be calculated as:\n\n\\[ N_s = \\frac{120 \\times 60}{4} = 1800 \\text{ RPM} \\]",
